<br>
As a necro, our buffs are pretty much non-existant (other than self only shielding spell) so the buff one doesn't help.<br>
<br>
The DD one doesn't help us because of the other effects on our DD spells (like the one that makes a giant into a skele, giant banes dont work.. but neither do undead spells) /shrug so that focus item doesn't help us at all either.<br>
<br>
Most of our spells have an extremely long cast time so the one that decreases casting time is the truly appeasing one of the bunch.  <br>
<br>
The one that decreases mana used is helpful, but as a necro, mana conservation isn't as much of a problem as for most casters.  With that said, ANY extra mana is ALWAYS more than welcome, so cant complain about this one.<br>
<br>
The ones to save components will be nice for resummoning pets to get stronger ones, but a decent level necro can get a stack of BC in no time, or buy a stack for 2-5 pp.  If they save us that ungodly coffin cost, they'll be AWESOME IMHO.<br>
<br>
Overall, they weren't too much of a help to necros.  They dont affect our DD's, nor do they affect our DOT's either by causing them to do more damage or last longer.  I do think they're a wonderful addition towards casters in general and a nice step towards starting the &quot;caster&quot; balancing but not the caster &quot;class&quot; balancing.<br>
<br>
Desbarolis:  I think mages would prefer not to have to resummon jewelry for their entire raid every 30 minutes or so.  If people are crude enough to use a mage for items and then deny them a group, simply put them on the &quot;no way in hell shall I summon you anything in the future&quot; list.  For kicks, I would list those people on the R&amp;F forum.  If other mages neglected them as well, they'd probably change their attitudes.  With that said, with the new items, mages and wizzies should be rocking out damage, so I think the groups will be more than happy to pick one up when available. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=9312.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=9312.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9312.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=9312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.threadControl?topicID=9312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9312.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9312.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td alig